into two sets, or partitioned,

01:16:53.316 --> 01:17:01.360
and we'll call them a
left set, and a right set,

01:17:01.360 --> 01:17:17.330
so that all the edges connect
a node in the left set,

01:17:17.330 --> 01:17:21.190
to a node in the right set.

01:17:23.759 --> 01:17:25.300
So in fact, a lot
of today we've been

01:17:25.300 --> 01:17:28.500
looking at bipartite graphs,
because the nodes are here.

01:17:28.500 --> 01:17:32.660
Like the men, and the women, and
the edges only go from the left

01:17:32.660 --> 01:17:33.900
to the right.

01:17:33.900 --> 01:17:35.335
And that is called bipartite.

01:17:35.335 --> 01:17:37.290
And it's called
bipartite because you

01:17:37.290 --> 01:17:41.820
can do it with two
colors, or in two pieces.

01:17:41.820 --> 01:17:43.860
So you don't win
a million dollars

